Texts.Eng: After continuous testing with various lab rats, the Bot of Terror ended up acting VERY suspicious. We attempted fixing our project, but out of nowhere it started shooting a couple bullets at one of the scientists. That's when we realized that we forgot to build a kill switch in case scenarios like this happened.

Entry Number 18
The Bot of Terror's behavior started becoming very severe, wrecking the facility with a strange, metallic substance; we had to initiate lockdown on the whole facility.

Unfortunately, we HAD to destroy our creation, but it fought back and caused several casualties. It started shooting out smaller copies of itself. This action was not normal, and we knew we never added that behavior into the code.
